This paper is about comparing the performance of two iterative algorithms in approximating Nash equilibrium in multiplayer games. This topic falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The comparison of the algorithms involves analyzing their convergence rates and approximation errors, which are related to topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical significance of the results, which is related to topics in statistics and machine learning (cs.SI).
